docs.abstract: The Securities and Exchange Commission is looking into the departure of a Goldman partner who had complained about misconduct.
docs.snippet: The Securities and Exchange Commission is looking into the departure of a Goldman partner who had complained about misconduct.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Securities and Exchange Commission has opened an inquiry into the departure of a senior investment banker and Goldman Sachs partner who raised concerns about what he viewed as unethical conduct at the bank, according to people briefed on the inquiry.

headline.main: Regulator Seeks Information About Goldman Sachs Ethics Complaint
headline.print_headline: Goldman Partner’s Exit Draws Scrutiny of S.E.C.

docs.abstract: The seizure of email records from a Times reporter alarmed First Amendment groups. Her relationship with an intelligence aide set off an ethical debate.
docs.snippet: The seizure of email records from a Times reporter alarmed First Amendment groups. Her relationship with an intelligence aide set off an ethical debate.
docs.lead_paragraph: The pearl bracelet arrived in May 2014, in the spring of Ali Watkins’s senior year in college, a graduation gift from a man many years her senior. It was the sort of bauble that might imply something more deeply felt than friendship — but then again, might not.

headline.main: How an Affair Between a Reporter and a Security Aide Has Rattled Washington Media
headline.print_headline: How Affair Between Journalist  And Senate Aide Rattled Media

byline.original: By Michael M. Grynbaum, Scott Shane and Emily Flitter

docs.abstract: Since the Whole Foods sale a year ago, traditional grocers have agreed to a variety of deals and partnerships. The latest investment is a Japanese chain’s $110 million stake in Boxed.
docs.snippet: Since the Whole Foods sale a year ago, traditional grocers have agreed to a variety of deals and partnerships. The latest investment is a Japanese chain’s $110 million stake in Boxed.
docs.lead_paragraph: Chieh Huang spent years trying to get grocery industry executives excited about the technology at Boxed, his grocery e-commerce company. He regularly gave tours of the company’s state-of-the-art fulfillment centers, featuring a custom software system and roving bands of autonomous carts.

headline.main: Amazon’s Ripple Effect on Grocery Industry: Rivals Stock Up on Start-Ups
headline.print_headline: Chasing Amazon, Grocers Stock Up on Start-Ups

docs.abstract: Slack’s appetite for funding and its eye-popping leaps in valuation are becoming normal in the private investment market.
docs.snippet: Slack’s appetite for funding and its eye-popping leaps in valuation are becoming normal in the private investment market.
docs.lead_paragraph: Slack, the four-year-old workplace messaging company, said on Tuesday that it had raised $427 million in new funding, just a year after its last huge infusion of money. The latest round values the company at $7.1 billion.

headline.main: Slack Raises $427 Million More, at $7.1 Billion Valuation
headline.print_headline: Slack’s Value Tops $7 Billion as Money Pours In

docs.abstract: The company rejects Silicon Valley’s aggressive, hype-driven way of doing business. But its slow and steady approach has frustrated some investors and employees.
docs.snippet: The company rejects Silicon Valley’s aggressive, hype-driven way of doing business. But its slow and steady approach has frustrated some investors and employees.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Ben Silbermann does not enjoy being interviewed. He isn’t a fan of speaking at tech industry conferences. Nor does he like sitting for glossy magazine portraits. He doesn’t think he should have to explain Pinterest, the web service that allows people to save images to virtual pinboards, to anyone other than those who want to use it.

headline.main: Pinterest Is a Unicorn. It Just Doesn’t Act Like One.
headline.print_headline: Will Pinterest Prove a Saner Model, or Wash Out?

docs.abstract: Drug Store, a new health-drink outlet in New York, is betting that customers will pay by text message after grabbing a bottle.
docs.snippet: Drug Store, a new health-drink outlet in New York, is betting that customers will pay by text message after grabbing a bottle.
docs.lead_paragraph: First there was self-checkout. Then Amazon’s cashier-free Go stores. Now there’s pay when you feel like it — we trust you.

headline.main: Paying Is Voluntary at This Selfie-Friendly Store
headline.print_headline: Payment Is on the Honor System at This Selfie-Friendly Manhattan Store

docs.abstract: The willingness to back some nicotine start-ups while condemning others illustrates the delicate ethical dance that investors are trying to perform.
docs.snippet: The willingness to back some nicotine start-ups while condemning others illustrates the delicate ethical dance that investors are trying to perform.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Silicon Valley’s investors have put their money in plenty of ethically dubious companies, including those that make addictive apps, surveillance technology or services that knowingly exploit legal gray areas.

headline.main: Silicon Valley Investors Shunned Juul, but Back Other Nicotine Start-Ups
headline.print_headline: Potential for Profit, But at What Cost?

docs.abstract: The Justice Department, F.B.I. and S.E.C. are broadening investigations or starting inquiries into Facebook over its leak of user data to Cambridge Analytica.
docs.snippet: The Justice Department, F.B.I. and S.E.C. are broadening investigations or starting inquiries into Facebook over its leak of user data to Cambridge Analytica.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Facebook said on Monday that it faced an expansion of federal investigations into its sharing of user data with the political consulting firm Cambridge Analytica, with more government agencies inquiring about the matter and examining the social network’s statements about the episode.

headline.main: Facebook Faces Broadened Federal Investigations Over Data and Privacy
headline.print_headline: Facebook Under More Scrutiny Over Data Sharing

headline.print_headline: E.U. Clears Luxembourg Over McDonald’s Tax Deal
